<subSubSection id="C3136AEB5756FFB2FF085FE2FE172640" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB639605756FFB2FF085FE2FE1F2730" blockId="17.[151,1437,1450,2017]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FF085FE2FEC4248D" bold="true" box="[151,371,1450,1476]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Revised diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35756FFB2FE775FE3FD7E248C" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[488,713,1451,1477]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladifer">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FE775FE3FD7E248C" box="[488,713,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Simonurius gladifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35756FFB2FC3D5FE3FAB2248C" authority="(Simon, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[930,1285,1451,1477]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratarius">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FC3D5FE3FBEE248C" box="[930,1113,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Si. quadratarius</emphasis>
(Simon, 1901)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844915756FFB2FADB5FE3FF6524A0" author="Galiano, M. E." pageId="17" pageNumber="448" pagination="273 - 470" refId="ref17277" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1963) Las especies americanas de aranas de la familia Salticidae descriptas por Eugene Simon: Redescripciones basadas en los ejemplares tipicos. Physis, 23 (66), 273 - 470." type="journal article" year="1963">Galiano 1963</bibRefCitation>
, figs 3 
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FEBE5F87FE9824A0" bold="true" box="[289,303,1487,1513]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">–</emphasis>
5) in the finger-like RTA with one long lobe, and the handle-shaped RvTA projecting retrolaterally (
<figureCitation id="133225E55756FFB2FF005FBBFE952747" box="[159,290,1523,1550]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–64" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-18@19.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 59–64. Scanning electronic microscopy (SEM). Male palp of Guriurius minuano sp. nov. (MCTP 38993): 59 ventral view, arrow: tegulum depression; 60 ventral view, arrow: ventral surface RvTA. Male palp of At. segmentatus (MCN 36806): 61 ventral view; 62 detail of RvTA dorsal surface. Male palp of Si. gladifer (MCTP 31078): 63 ventral view, arrow: tegulum depression; 64 details of RvTA arrow: RvTA ventral surface." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417700/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Figs 63–64</figureCitation>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35756FFB2FE035FBBFDAF2744" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[412,536,1523,1549]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladifer">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FE035FBBFDAF2744" box="[412,536,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Si. gladifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35756FFB2FD625FBBFC042744" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[765,947,1523,1549]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratarius">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FD625FBBFC042744" box="[765,947,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Si. quadratarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the straight RTA. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35756FFB2FABE5FBBFA2A2744" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1313,1437,1523,1549]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladifer">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FABE5FBBFA2A2744" box="[1313,1437,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Si. gladifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35756FFB2FEF65C5FFD322778" authority="(Galiano, 1985)" authorityName="Marta &amp; Bustamante &amp; Ruiz &amp; Teixeira &amp; Hagopián &amp; Brescovit &amp; Valiati &amp; Rodrigues" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Galiano" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[361,645,1558,1585]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisac" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FEF65C5FFE7D2779" box="[361,458,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Si. pisac</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844915756FFB2FE455C5FFDCA2778" author="Galiano, M. E." box="[474,637,1558,1585]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" pagination="9 - 18" refId="ref17368" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1985) Revision del genero Hurius Simon, 1901 (Araneae, Salticidae). Journal of Arachnology, 13, 9 - 18." type="journal article" year="1985">Galiano, 1985</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FD115C5FFCA72778" bold="true" box="[654,784,1559,1585]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24E58095756FFB2FD115C5FFCA72778" box="[654,784,1559,1585]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844915756FFB2FCD05C5FFC5C2778" author="Galiano, M. E." box="[847,1003,1558,1585]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" pagination="9 - 18" refId="ref17368" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1985) Revision del genero Hurius Simon, 1901 (Araneae, Salticidae). Journal of Arachnology, 13, 9 - 18." type="journal article" year="1985">Galiano 1985</bibRefCitation>
, figs 22–24) in the inverted U-shaped atrium and the long posteriorly placed S2, but differs by having larger and horizontal S1 surpassing the border of the atrium (
<figureCitation id="133225E55756FFB2FE875C17FE2C2730" box="[280,411,1630,1657]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–58" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[173,1409,421,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-133@18.[151,1435,417,1845]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 49–58. Simonurius gladifer. Habitus male (MCTP 31078): 49 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 50 ventral view; 51 lateral view; 52 face, frontal view; Habitus female (MCTP 31069): 53 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 54 ventral view; 55 lateral view; 56 face, frontal view, scale bars: 1 mm. Epigyne female (MCTP 31082): 57 ventral view; 58 dorsal view, white arrow: S2* is broken but illustrated and S1 angular axis in anterior region, scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417698/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">
Figs 57 
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FEF25C17FECC2730" bold="true" box="[365,379,1631,1657]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">–</emphasis>
58
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB639605756FFB2FF585CCAFE172640" blockId="17.[151,1437,1450,2017]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725756FFB2FF585CCAFE1327D5" bold="true" box="[199,420,1666,1692]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Epigyne variation.</emphasis>
There is a variation in size, shape, and angle between the S1 among the specimens studied, i.e., anterior apex of S1 closer or separated by a brief v-shaped gap between them (
<figureCitation id="133225E55756FFB2FBF85CEFFB0B2788" box="[1127,1212,1702,1729]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–58" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[173,1409,421,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-133@18.[151,1435,417,1845]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 49–58. Simonurius gladifer. Habitus male (MCTP 31078): 49 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 50 ventral view; 51 lateral view; 52 face, frontal view; Habitus female (MCTP 31069): 53 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 54 ventral view; 55 lateral view; 56 face, frontal view, scale bars: 1 mm. Epigyne female (MCTP 31082): 57 ventral view; 58 dorsal view, white arrow: S2* is broken but illustrated and S1 angular axis in anterior region, scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417698/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
, see arrow). It was observed that the fertilization ducts may be closer to each other in anterior region dorsally to spermathecae or more distant from each other.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
